btls / btls-sys (0.5.6, crates.io)
----------------------------------
A hard fork of BoringSSL with a `prefix-symbols` feature (objcopy-prefixes the BoringSSL
symbols so they coexist with OpenSSL in one binary). Backs the `Stack::Boring` egress
backend. BoringSSL is distributed under a mix of the OpenSSL License, the
original SSLeay license, and the ISC license; see the BoringSSL source for full terms.

openssl / openssl-sys (crates.io), vendored via openssl-src (OpenSSL 3.6.3)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Backs the `Stack::OpenSsl` egress backend. OpenSSL 3.x is
licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

rustls 0.23.37 / aws-lc-rs (crates.io)
--------------------------------------
Backs the `Stack::RustlsAwsLc` egress backend used by the Grok client profile.
rustls is licensed under Apache-2.0, ISC, and MIT terms; aws-lc-rs is licensed
under ISC and Apache-2.0 terms. See their packaged license files for details.

CA root bundle — src/ca-bundle.pem
----------------------------------
Derived from the OpenBSD `cert.pem` (lineage: Mozilla NSS, MPL-2.0). The original
`$OpenBSD: cert.pem,v ...$` provenance header is retained in the file. The enclave runtime
has no system trust store, so this bundle is compiled in (`include_bytes!`) and used to
validate upstream server certificates.

